statement.p:
Define
f(t)= \begin{cases} t+2t^2\sin\left(\dfrac{1}{t^2}\right), & t\ne0,\\[2mm] 0, & t=0. \end{cases}
Then f'(0)=1. So the derivative at the origin is nonzero.
